        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 7:17PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 717 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 7 miles east of Pinon to 7 miles north of
Pueblo Depot. Movement was northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hanover.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
